        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>We
conservatively assume the lower limit on the SFR 
not corrected for dust extinction (6.7Msun/yr). 
We convert this minimum SFR into [CII] luminosity by exploiting the calibration by Sargsyan et al.
(2012), yielding 0.077 Jy km/s.
We recall that these are conservative estimates, since this SFR assumes no dust 
correction
To achieve an accuracy on the redshift of $\Delta$z=0.0005, 
we require (according to our past experience,
Maiolino et al 2005, 2009) a S/N&gt;5 in velocity bins of 25~km/s.
We assume a line width of 50km/s, conservatively larger than what we find in 
the z=7.1 galaxy that we detected in Cycle1.

The source is nearly unresolved in HST images, so we can safely assume a point-like morphology.


We do not aim at any detection of the continuum.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
